{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop Child Maintenance if parents are denied access to their children",
        "additional_details": "We are calling on the UK Government to introduce a new law that:\r\n- Links child maintenance to parental access \u2013 If a parent is refused access without a valid reason, payments should be paused until fair contact is arranged\r\n- Encourages fair co-parenting \u2013 Prevents one parent from using the child as leverage \r\n- Reduces legal costs \u2013 Parents should not have to pay mediation and court fees just to see their child",
        "background": "We believe that parents, often Fathers, across the UK are paying child maintenance while being unfairly denied access to their children and we want this to change. ",
